==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carpophyte
<hw>Car"po*phyte</hw> <pr>(k⟦aum⟧r"p⟦osl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>karpo`s</grk> fruit + <grk>fyto`n</grk> plant.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A flowerless plant which forms a true fruit as
the result of fertilization, as the red seaweeds, the
<fam>Ascomycetes</fam>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The division of alg⟦ae⟧ and fungi into four classes
called Carpophytes, Oophytes, Protophytes, and Zygophytes (or
<class>Carpospore⟦ae⟧</class>, <class>Oospore⟦ae⟧</class>,
<class>Protophyta</class>, and <class>Zygospore⟦ae⟧</class>) was
proposed by Sachs about 1875.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carpospore</ent>⟦br⟧
